==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Dioxindol
<hw>Di`ox*in"dol</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[Pref.
<ets>di-</ets> + <ets>ox</ets>ygen + <ets>indol</ets>.]</ety>
<fld>(Chem.)</fld> <def>A white, crystalline, nitrogenous substance
obtained by the reduction of isatin. It is a member of the indol series;
-- hence its name.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

